# PokeManiac Compose Patterns

> **Guiding principle:** All patterns here are applied pragmatically. Complexity is only justified by a visible, concrete benefit. Code must remain readable by a senior Android developer who doesn't know this codebase. When in doubt, prefer the simpler solution. See `pokemaniac-guide.mdc` for the full engineering philosophy.

## Screen vs View Pattern

### Screen (Container Composable)
**Location:** Feature module root, file name: `*Screen.kt`

**Responsibilities:**
- Collect `StateFlow` with lifecycle awareness using `collectAsStateWithLifecycle()`
- Observe lifecycle events
- Handle error flows with `LaunchedEffect`
- Show snackbars
- Inject ViewModel via `koinViewModel()`

```kotlin
@Composable
fun MyFeatureScreen(
    modifier: Modifier = Modifier,
    viewModel: MyFeatureViewModel = koinViewModel(),
    lifecycleOwner: LifecycleOwner = LocalLifecycleOwner.current
) {
    val snackbarHostState = remember { SnackbarHostState() }

    // Error handling — lifecycle-aware: pauses when app is in background
    viewModel.error.observeWithLifecycle(lifecycleOwner) { error ->
        snackbarHostState.showSnackbar(error.message)  // UiError.message is always non-null
    }
    
    // State collection — lifecycle-aware: pauses when app is in background
    val uiState by viewModel.uiState.collectAsStateWithLifecycle()
    
    // Lifecycle callback to reload on start
    // Use ON_RESUME instead if data can change from another Activity (e.g. after camera flow)
    OnLifecycleEventEffect(Lifecycle.Event.ON_START, lifecycleOwner) { viewModel.start() }
    
    // Stable lambda — only wrap in remember() if this screen contains a LazyList/LazyGrid/animation
    val context = LocalContext.current
    val onNavigate = remember(viewModel, context) { { viewModel.navigateSomewhere(context) } }

    // Delegate to stateless View
    MyFeatureView(
        modifier = modifier,
        uiState = uiState,
        snackbarHostState = snackbarHostState,
        onAction = viewModel::onAction,
        onNavigate = onNavigate
    )
}
```

### View (Stateless Composable)
**Location:** Feature module `ui/` folder, file name: `*View.kt`

**Responsibilities:**
- Pure UI rendering
- NO state collection
- NO side effects
- Accept all data and callbacks as parameters
- Include `@Preview` composables

```kotlin
@Composable
fun MyFeatureView(
    modifier: Modifier = Modifier,
    uiState: MyFeatureUiState,
    snackbarHostState: SnackbarHostState,
    onAction: (action: UserAction) -> Unit = {},
    onNavigate: (destination: String) -> Unit = {}
) {
    Scaffold(
        modifier = modifier.fillMaxSize(),
        snackbarHost = { SnackbarHost(snackbarHostState) },
        topBar = {
            MyFeatureTopBar(
                onNavigateBack = { onNavigate("back") }
            )
        }
    ) { padding ->
        Box(modifier = Modifier.padding(padding)) {
            when (uiState) {
                MyFeatureUiState.Loading -> GenericLoader()
                is MyFeatureUiState.Data -> {
                    MyFeatureContent(
                        items = uiState.items,
                        onAction = onAction
                    )
                }
                MyFeatureUiState.EmptyResult -> {
                    GenericEmptyScreen()
                }
            }
        }
    }
}
```

