## Recomposition Optimization

Compose skips recomposing a function only when all its parameters are **stable AND equal** to the previous call. Unstable types or new lambda instances on every recomposition prevent skipping.

### When to optimize — pragmatic tiers

Optimization has a cost in code complexity. Apply the full set of optimizations only where recomposition problems are actually **visible** to the user.

**Tier 1 — Always apply (zero or negligible complexity cost):**
- `@Immutable` / `@Stable` on UiState and UI models — one annotation, no logic change
- `PersistentList<>` for all collection fields — already the project standard
- `observeWithLifecycle()` for all SharedFlow — replaces old pattern 1:1, also a correctness fix
- `rememberUpdatedState` for callbacks in `observeWithLifecycle` — 1 extra line, correctness fix
- `key = { it.id }` on all lazy `items { }` — prevents item recomposition on reorder
- String `key` on all single `item { }` blocks in lazy layouts — `item(key = "header") { ... }`
- `remember(param) { }` for any value derived inline from a parameter (sumOf, filter, count…)

**Tier 2 — Apply only on screens with LazyList, LazyGrid, or animations:**
- `remember(viewModel, context) { ... }` for navigation lambdas — adds lines, only pays off when child composables inside a scrolling list can actually skip
- Pass only the fields a composable actually uses — see "Recomposition Scope" section below

**This project's Tier 2 screens** (have LazyColumn / LazyVerticalGrid):
- `DashboardScreen` — LazyColumn with live feed + pull-to-refresh
- `SearchFriendScreen` — LazyVerticalGrid + frequent state changes from search
- `MyFriendListScreen` — LazyColumn of friends
- `MyFriendDetailScreen` — LazyVerticalGrid of cards
- `MyProfileScreen` — LazyVerticalGrid of cards

**Not worth optimizing** (simple, static, no list/animation):
- `PostTransactionStep1Screen` — camera flow, single interaction
- `PostTransactionStep2Screen` — plain form
- `BillingScreen` — stub/placeholder

