## Type-Safe Navigation with Serialization

In features that need internal navigation:

```kotlin
sealed class Routes {
    @Serializable
    data object List : Routes()
    
    @Serializable
    data class Detail(val id: String) : Routes()  // ID only — no display data
}

@Composable
fun MyFeatureNavHost(navController: NavHostController) {
    NavHost(
        navController = navController,
        startDestination = Routes.List
    ) {
        composable<Routes.List> {
            MyListScreen(
                onItemClick = { itemId ->
                    navController.navigate(Routes.Detail(itemId))
                }
            )
        }
        composable<Routes.Detail> { backStackEntry ->
            val args: Routes.Detail = backStackEntry.toRoute()
            MyDetailScreen(id = args.id)  // Screen loads its own data from the ViewModel
        }
    }
}
```

### ✅ Navigation Routes Carry IDs Only — Not Display Data

Routes must only contain the **identifier** needed to load the data — never display data like `name`, `description`, or `imageUrl`.

**Why:** If a route carries `name` and the API also returns a `name`, you have two sources of truth. They can diverge, and the View would need to decide which one to trust.

```kotlin
// ❌ BAD — name duplicated: also present in MyDetailUiState.Data.friend.name
data class Detail(val id: String, val name: String) : Routes()

// Screen has a dual source of truth: friendName from args AND state.friend.name from the API
MyDetailView(friendName = args.name, uiState = uiState)  // which one is correct?

// ✅ GOOD — only the ID travels via navigation
data class Detail(val id: String) : Routes()

// The View derives everything it needs from uiState — single source of truth
@Composable
fun MyDetailView(uiState: MyDetailUiState, ...) {
    val name = if (uiState is Data) uiState.friend.name else ""
    Scaffold(topBar = { TopBar(title = name) }) { ... }
}
```

**Consequence for the top bar:** While loading, the title will be empty. This is acceptable — the loading state shows a spinner, not a title. Once data loads, the real name from the API appears. Never add a separate `name` parameter to a `*View` composable just to pre-populate the toolbar during loading.
